PN,30703
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1783741698
OL,3,CUS demands Iran publicly guarantees
OL,4,CStrait of Hormuz is open and safe for
OL,5,Cships
OL,7,FEnding Tehran's stranglehold on the
OL,8,Fsea route, which disrupted global oil
OL,9,Fand gas supplies and drove up fuel and
OL,10,Ffood prices, had been a key demand in
OL,11,Fprevious negotiations.
OL,13,FHowever, the initial deal reached
OL,14,Fbetween the US and Iran only provides
OL,15,Ffor safe, toll-free passage of the
OL,16,Fwaterway for 60 days, pending the
OL,17,Foutcome of a final agreement on
OL,18,FTehran's disputed nuclear plans.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30704
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1783741698
OL,3,CUS demands Iran publicly guarantees
OL,4,CStrait of Hormuz is open and safe for
OL,5,Cships
OL,7,FThe pact also leaves it to Iran and
OL,8,FOman, in conjunction with other Gulf
OL,9,Fstates, to "define the future
OL,10,Fadministration and maritime services
OL,11,Fin the Strait of Hormuz".
OL,13,FIn the meantime, Iran has continued to
OL,14,Ftry to exert leverage over the
OL,15,Fchannel, including demanding ships
OL,16,Fseek permission to transit and raising
OL,17,Fthe spectre of future charges.
OL,26,@qD@LOUsD@XO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
