OL,3,CUS demands Iran publicly guarantees
OL,4,CStrait of Hormuz is open and safe for
OL,5,Cships
OL,7,FPrior to the latest flare-up,
OL,8,Fnegotiations between the two sides had
OL,9,Fbeen due to restart following the
OL,10,Fburial of Iran's late supreme leader
OL,11,FAyatollah Ali Khamenei, who was killed
OL,12,Fon the first day of the conflict.
OL,14,FMediators are engaged in frantic
OL,15,Fdiplomatic efforts to try and salvage
OL,16,Fthe tattered peace process.
OL,18,FAt the same time, Israel has said it
OL,19,Fstands ready to confront Iran again if
OL,20,Fneeded.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
